					<description><![CDATA[Since the beginning of this trip, Ian and I have known that at some point we would want to drink madeira in Madeira. Â But, other than its viticulture, we knew very little about the island (actually an archipelago, but Madeira&#8230; <a href="/index.php/2015/11/08/paradise-in-madeira/" class="more-link">Continue Reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Since the beginning of this trip, Ian and I have known that at some point we would want to drink madeira in Madeira. Â But, other than its viticulture, we knew very little about the island (actually an archipelago, but Madeira is also the name of the largest island, a la Hawaii). Â As it turns out, this place is a tropical paradise.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4053.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1383 aligncenter" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4053-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_4053" width="640" height="480" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4053-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4053-500x375.jpg 500w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4053.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><span id="more-1388"></span></p>
<p>We rented a car from the airport in Funchal to drive across the island to Porto Moniz. Â We spent most of the drive with our mouths open, in awe of the scenery around us. Â Green cliffs and waterfalls would appear out of nowhere.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3962.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1377 aligncenter" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3962-768x1024.jpg" alt="IMG_3962" width="640" height="853" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3962-768x1024.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3962-375x500.jpg 375w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3962.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>
<p>Sometimes we also had to yield to cows:</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4014.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1380 aligncenter" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4014-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_4014" width="640" height="480" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4014-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4014-500x375.jpg 500w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4014.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>
<p>And even though some of the roads were the scariest we&#8217;ve ever driven on, we were still instantly smitten with Madeira.</p>
<div id="attachment_1381" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4016.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1381" class="size-large wp-image-1381" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4016-768x1024.jpg" alt="Can't really capture just how incredibly steep some of these roads were." width="640" height="853" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4016-768x1024.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4016-375x500.jpg 375w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_4016.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-1381" class="wp-caption-text">Can&#8217;t really capture just how incredibly steep some of these roads were.</p></div>
<p>We stayed at the amazing Aqua Natura, which we can&#8217;t recommend highly enough. Â The natural pools, seafront balconies, fresh breakfasts, and low rates captured our hearts and we promised we would return.</p>
<div id="attachment_1374" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3943.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1374" class="wp-image-1374 size-large" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3943-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_3943" width="640" height="480" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3943-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3943-500x375.jpg 500w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3943.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-1374" class="wp-caption-text">Natural pools, filled with sea water during high tide.</p></div>
<div id="attachment_1373" style="width: 650px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3929.jpg"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1373" class="wp-image-1373 size-large" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3929-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_3929" width="640" height="480" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3929-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3929-500x375.jpg 500w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3929.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a><p id="caption-attachment-1373" class="wp-caption-text">View from our balcony. We would have paid extra for this balcony, but every room has one exactly like it!</p></div>
<p>One day we took a hike to this beautiful place:</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3975.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1379 aligncenter" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3975-768x1024.jpg" alt="IMG_3975" width="640" height="853" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3975-768x1024.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3975-375x500.jpg 375w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3975.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>
<p>The trail was along the levadas, which are irrigation channels that run all over the island. Â The entire hike was really lush.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3959.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1376 aligncenter" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3959-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_3959" width="640" height="480" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3959-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3959-500x375.jpg 500w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3959.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>
<p>Some of it also looked spooky:</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3972.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1378 aligncenter" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3972-768x1024.jpg" alt="IMG_3972" width="640" height="853" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3972-768x1024.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3972-375x500.jpg 375w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3972.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>
<p>We half-expected pterodactyls to appearÂ at any moment.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3958.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-1375 aligncenter" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3958-1024x768.jpg" alt="IMG_3958" width="640" height="480" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3958-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3958-500x375.jpg 500w, /wp-content/uploads/2015/11/IMG_3958.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a></p>
<p>We&#8217;ve moved on to the largest city, Funchal, but Madeira continues to be excellent in every way. Â More updates to follow!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
